---
---
<section class="for-whom" id="forWhom">
  <div class="fw-inner">
    <div class="fw-header">
      <div class="fw-eyebrow">Use Cases</div>
      <h2 class="fw-title">
        Built for any structured conversation <em>worth having more of.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="fw-sub">
        One platform. Six wedges of work where the interview is the bottleneck —
        and a long tail of others coming.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="fw-tabs" role="tablist">
      <button class="fw-tab active" data-tab="hiring" role="tab" aria-selected="true">Hiring</button>
      <button class="fw-tab" data-tab="discovery" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Customer Discovery</button>
      <button class="fw-tab" data-tab="research" role="tab" aria-selected="false">User Research</button>
      <button class="fw-tab" data-tab="audit" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Audits</button>
      <button class="fw-tab" data-tab="legal" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Legal</button>
      <button class="fw-tab" data-tab="hr" role="tab" aria-selected="false">HR</button>
    </div>

    <!-- HIRING -->
    <div class="fw-panel active" data-panel="hiring" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          You have 200 candidates and time to talk to <em>twenty</em>.
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          The other 180 are getting away. Recruiters and staffing agencies lose great candidates
          because the first-round conversation can't scale. AnyInterview conducts those screens
          in your voice — qualifying, qualifying, qualifying — until your inbox is full of
          people actually worth your time.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Voice + video screens</strong> with real-time follow-ups, not preset video questions into the void.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Cheating-proof technical proctoring</strong> for engineering hires — no surveillance theater.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Structured, EEOC-compliant</strong> question flows — every candidate, the same fair conversation.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Multilingual support</strong> for high-volume hiring across markets.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how recruiters use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · 47 in queue</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">Senior Backend Engineer</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">45 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice + Video</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Proctored</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>Tell me about a system you've built that you're proud of — what made it work?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>How would you approach designing a rate-limiting system for a high-traffic API?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>Tell me about a time a system you owned failed — what did you learn?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 12 questions shown</span>
          <span class="right">Reviewing 4 transcripts</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DISCOVERY -->
    <div class="fw-panel" data-panel="discovery" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          You were supposed to do 50 customer interviews. <em>You've done four.</em>
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          Every founder knows the YC commandment. Almost no founder follows it. AnyInterview talks
          to your customers when you can't — asking the questions you'd ask, recording every word,
          and handing you back the patterns. The discovery you've been promising your investors,
          finally done.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>JTBD-style protocols</strong> built in — or describe your own in chat.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Curious, unleading voice</strong> — no pitching, no validation-seeking.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Cross-interview synthesis</strong> — patterns surfaced across dozens of conversations.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Free tier</strong> for early-stage founders — start without paying.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how founders use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · 12 completed</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">SaaS Onboarding Discovery</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">30 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">JTBD</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>Walk me through how onboarding works for a new customer at your company today.</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>Where in that flow do you feel the most friction — yours or theirs?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>If you could wave a magic wand and change one thing, what would it be?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 9 questions shown</span>
          <span class="right">Synthesis ready</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RESEARCH -->
    <div class="fw-panel" data-panel="research" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          You're one researcher for an 80-person product team. <em>Stop being the bottleneck.</em>
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          AnyInterview runs your interview protocols across dozens of participants in parallel —
          the same questions you'd ask, in your voice, with the rigor your work requires.
          Insight velocity, finally caught up to ship velocity.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Protocol library</strong> — save and reuse interview structures across studies.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Voice + screen recording</strong> for moderated usability sessions.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Neutral, patient interviewer voice</strong> — designed not to lead.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Cross-participant theming</strong> — patterns surfaced as they emerge.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how research teams use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · 18 in field</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">Checkout Flow Usability Study</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">25 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice + Screen</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Moderated</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>Walk me through what you'd normally do to complete a purchase.</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>What were you expecting to happen there?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>Looking back, where did your confidence dip?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 11 prompts shown</span>
          <span class="right">Themes emerging</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AUDIT -->
    <div class="fw-panel" data-panel="audit" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          Half your fieldwork is the same interview, <em>asked forty times.</em>
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          AnyInterview conducts control owner walkthroughs, fraud risk inquiries, and process
          documentation interviews — generating defensible, standards-aligned workpapers your
          senior staff can review instead of write. Built for SOC 2, internal audit, and beyond.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Control walkthrough templates</strong> aligned to common frameworks (SOC 2, ISO 27001, NIST).</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Workpaper-ready exports</strong> — formatted for AuditBoard, Workiva, and standalone.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Seven-year audit playback</strong> — every interview replayable for the full retention window.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Multi-jurisdictional</strong> support across timezones, languages, and business units.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how audit teams use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · SOC 2 fieldwork</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">Access Provisioning Walkthrough</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">30 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">CC6.1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>Walk me through how a new employee receives access to production systems.</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>Who approves the access request, and how is approval documented?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>What happens to access when an employee changes role or leaves?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 14 questions shown</span>
          <span class="right">Workpaper ready</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- LEGAL -->
    <div class="fw-panel" data-panel="legal" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          Your highest-paid people are doing intake. <em>That's the wrong people.</em>
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          AnyInterview conducts structured client intakes, witness statements, and pre-deposition
          prep — gathering case-relevant facts in a format your attorneys can act on. Privilege-aware.
          Ethics-compliant. Designed with practicing lawyers.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Practice-area templates</strong> for personal injury, immigration, family, and class action firms.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Privilege-aware design</strong> — every interview respects attorney-client boundaries.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Calm, careful interviewer voice</strong> — never gives legal advice, always discloses limits.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>HIPAA authorization</strong> and document collection workflows built in.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how law firms use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · 6 intakes today</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">Personal Injury Client Intake</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">20 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Privilege-aware</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>When and where did the incident occur?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>Walk me through what happened, in your own words.</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>What injuries did you sustain, and when did symptoms first appear?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 14 questions shown</span>
          <span class="right">Attorney-ready summary</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- HR -->
    <div class="fw-panel" data-panel="hr" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="fw-content">
        <h3 class="fw-pain">
          The conversations that matter most are the ones <em>you never have time for.</em>
        </h3>
        <p class="fw-narrative">
          Stay interviews. Exit interviews. Investigations. Skip-levels. AnyInterview makes
          them all possible — neutral, structured, evidence-grade — at a scale your team
          could never reach manually. The proactive HR function you've been trying to build.
        </p>
        <ul class="fw-features">
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Stay &amp; exit interview protocols</strong> built in — proven retention questions, ready to deploy.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Investigation-grade documentation</strong> — defensible records, structured questioning, full audit trail.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Neutral interviewer voice</strong> — employees share more candidly than they would with HR.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></span>
            <span><strong>Cross-team theming</strong> — surface patterns across departments and over time.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="fw-link">
          See how people teams use AnyInterview
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="fw-visual">
        <div class="fw-vis-eyebrow"><span class="live-dot"></span>Live · Q2 stay interviews</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-title">Top-Performer Stay Interview</div>
        <div class="fw-vis-meta">
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">20 min</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Voice</span>
          <span class="fw-vis-tag">Confidential</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-questions">
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">01</span><span>What's keeping you here right now?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">02</span><span>What's the most frustrating part of your work this quarter?</span></div>
          <div class="fw-vis-q"><span class="num">03</span><span>What would have to change for you to consider leaving?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fw-vis-status">
          <span>3 of 10 questions shown</span>
          <span class="right">Themes by team</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script>import '../scripts/for-whom-tabs.ts';</script>

<style>
  section.for-whom {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    padding: clamp(80px, 12vh, 140px) clamp(20px, 5vw, 56px);
  }

  .fw-inner {
    max-width: 1240px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .fw-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto clamp(48px, 7vh, 80px);
  }

  .fw-eyebrow {
    font-size: 11.5px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .fw-eyebrow::before, .fw-eyebrow::after {
    content: "";
    width: 22px; height: 1px;
    background: var(--rule);
  }

  h2.fw-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.6vw, 56px);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  h2.fw-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .fw-sub {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.4vw, 19px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-top: 18px;
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .fw-tabs {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }
  .fw-tab {
    padding: 14px 22px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    margin-bottom: -1px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.005em;
  }
  .fw-tab:hover { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .fw-tab.active {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .fw-panel {
    display: none;
    animation: fwPanelIn 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  }
  .fw-panel.active { display: grid; }

  .fw-panel {
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(40px, 6vw, 80px);
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1080px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .fw-content { padding-top: 8px; }

  .fw-pain {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(24px, 2.8vw, 36px);
    line-height: 1.18;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .fw-pain em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .fw-narrative {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  .fw-features {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .fw-features li {
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 14.5px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .fw-features li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .fw-features .check {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: 18px; height: 18px;
    margin-top: 2px;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .fw-features .check svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; stroke: currentColor; fill: none; stroke-width: 2.4; }
  .fw-features strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-right: 4px;
  }

  .fw-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: gap 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .fw-link:hover { gap: 12px; color: var(--accent-bright); }
  .fw-link svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; stroke: currentColor; fill: none; stroke-width: 2; }

  .fw-visual {
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 28px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    min-height: 320px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .fw-visual::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--accent), transparent);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .fw-vis-eyebrow {
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .fw-vis-eyebrow .live-dot {
    width: 7px; height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #2d8659;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(45,134,89,0.18);
  }

  .fw-vis-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .fw-vis-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .fw-vis-tag {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10.5px;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .fw-vis-questions {
    margin-top: 8px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .fw-vis-q {
    background: var(--field-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
